2026-05-17 17:56:40 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #7 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Compute percentage of failed samples (Enterococcus > 104) across provided Boston Harbor beach datasheets that had 1-Day Rain > 0. Use downloaded CSV files from kramabench-environment-hard-8. Print counts and percentage to two decimals.\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# load files using path map from download\nbase = Path('/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1731204_1779040557413')\nfiles = [\n    base / 'kramabench-environment-hard-8' / 'files' / 'constitution_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    base / 'kramabench-environment-hard-8' / 'files' / 'm_street_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    base / 'kramabench-environment-hard-8' / 'files' / 'carson_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    base / 'kramabench-environment-hard-8' / 'files' / 'city_point_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    base / 'kramabench-environment-hard-8' / 'files' / 'pleasure_bay_and_castle_island_beach_datasheet.csv',\n]\n\nall_rows = []\nfor f in files:\n    df = pd.read_csv(f, header=None, dtype=str)\n    # Find the header row with 'Date' and set columns from there\n    header_idx = None\n    for i, row in df.iterrows():\n        if 'Date' in row.astype(str).values:\n            header_idx = i\n            break\n    if header_idx is None:\n        continue\n    header = df.iloc[header_idx].fillna('').tolist()\n    data = df.iloc[header_idx+1:].copy()\n    data.columns = header\n    data = data.reset_index(drop=True)\n    # normalize columns: we expect '1-Day Rain' and Enterococcus columns possibly repeated per location\n    # Melt Enterococcus columns by finding columns containing 'Enterococcus' or 'Enterococcus'\n    # First identify rain col\n    rain_col = None\n    for col in data.columns:\n        if '1-Day Rain' in col:\n            rain_col = col\n            break\n    # Identify any columns that equal 'Enterococ